BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:VbzNuezlbUIc_nIk2OTZu
SUMMARY:Kids On The Brink: Raising Emotionally Healthy Youth
DTSTAMP:20260308T063046Z
DTSTART:20260319T120000Z
DESCRIPTION:Kids On The Brink: Raising Emotionally Healthy Youth \\nIn this
	 event\\\, Donna Jackson Nakazawa will combine cutting-edge science\\\, re
	al student voices\\\, and practical tools to help adults better support to
	day’s youth. \\nDonna will cover:\\n– The latest research on female brain 
	development\\n– The unprecedented challenges facing teens today and why so
	 many are in crisis\\n– How these factors impact youth mental health\\n– W
	hy social stress\\\, in particular\\\, is the most damaging type of stress
	 for kids\\n– How regulating ourselves helps our kids regulate their emoti
	ons \\nParticipants will gain:\\n– Actionable strategies parents\\\, famil
	ies\\\, and organizations can utilize to better support our youth\\n– 12 s
	cience-based steps for talking with youth in neuroprotective ways and buil
	ding healthier parent-child connection \\nDonna will also share highlights
	 from her national Post-It Note Project\\\, featuring insights from thousa
	nds of middle and high school students about what they wish their parents 
	and other adults understood—and did—differently. \\nThis event will be mod
	erated by Christy Keating from The Heartful Parent Collective.\n\nhttps://
	myballard.com/event/kids-on-the-brink-raising-emotionally-healthy-youth/\n
	\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/kids-on-the-brink-raising-emotionally-healt
	hy-youth/
LOCATION:Zoom
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zpt0jFcf6A6H8MZbWPGPs
SUMMARY:Book Release Party: A Change of Pace
DTSTAMP:20260308T063046Z
DTSTART:20260319T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Swoon City & Generous Press to celebrate the launch of “A 
	Change of Pace” by J.A. Stevens. \\n📚 Copy of A Change of Pace with signed
	 bookplate Included in the ticket price \\nEvent will feature: \\n📖 A read
	ing by Generous Press Co-founders \\n🍓Light bites and refreshments \\n🎭 Cr
	aft your own mask \\n📸 Photobooth \\n👯 Have a meet-cute with other bookish
	 folks \\n👗 Regency dress is encouraged \\nDescription of A Change of Pace
	: \\nThis sapphic historical romance brings “pride without prejudice” to R
	egency London. \\nAlthough cavalier with love\\\, the famously rakeish Mis
	s Georgina Pace is deeply concerned for the well being of others. And so w
	hen she learns that dear innocent Mr. Coombes has been targeted by a corru
	pt gaming house\\\, she will stop at nothing to protect him. Miss Pace’s q
	uest for justice leads her to the enigmatic Lady Mortimer\\\, who offers a
	ssistance while keeping her cards close to her chest. Will Miss Pace risk 
	it all—including her heart? \\nA Change of Pace reimagines a Regency Londo
	n free of the entrenched systems of oppression we expect\\\, putting a spe
	culative and hopeful lens onto the past.\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/bo
	ok-release-party-a-change-of-pace/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/book-release-party-a-change-of-pace/
LOCATION:Swoon City\\\, 1716 NW Market St\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98107\\\, 
	United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
